== Background ==

A new foraging network was set up as part of Pixelache 2010. As part of this a suomi kieli wiki was started in appropedia. Pispala Cultural Association ry, based in Pispala, Tampere came down and held a kasvitietotalkoot. This was successful and more talkoots will be held to spread the idea. The Pispala stuff was developed independently from the Helsinki Pixelache stuff, but synergy and co-operation seemed sensible. So it will be with other foraging things around the world.

The uniqueness is not foraging per se, but rather guides, botanical signs and talkoots to facilitate that.   

Ruoanetsintä (foraging)

Etsitään ruokaa metsästä. It was done by Pisplan Kulttuuri yhditsys ry after they ran several permacultuuri päivät. In the picture can be seen the leader of a foraging walk in Pispala as part of those päivät.


== Methods ==

A series of signs will be made targeted at different audiences. Images of useful plants will be added to short texts. This will be done by using talkoots and led walks, events and guide books etc. In Helsinki at the Ptarmigan Arts Centre residents were asked, during a talkoot, which plants were growing usefully in the region. These were then shortlisted to 8 plants that were useful, safe for usage and clearly identifiable in suomi kieli and English and the Latin taxa. Signs were then made for these and given away during Pixelache 2010.

